alwaysApply: true
---
- each .h file in external/Headers should have a port in rust in a form of a single .rs file if there is only one type declared in .h, or a rust module in a form of a directory with mod.rs and dedicated .rs files if there are multiple types declared in .h.
- rust file names should be in camel case w/o mtl or mtl4 prefix
- if multiple types in rust are found, it should be split into multiple, so each .rs file contain only one type declaration
- all files in rust shoud be grouped by modules with names, corresponding to the original .h file name
- all original documentation of .h should be copied to .rs with the only allowed change in the mentioned type names following rust doc convention 